cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper discusses a neural network model called 2-Layers Sparse Predictive Coding (2L-SPC) and compares it with a Hierarchical Lasso (Hi-La) network. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on efficiently representing multi-dimensional, structured data such as images using Hierarchical Sparse Coding (HSC). 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the impact of inter-layer feedback connections on the performance of the 2L-SPC model and compares it with the Hi-La model. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new neural network model and evaluates its performance on different databases. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) - Although less likely, the paper's focus on hierarchical sparse coding could also be relevant to sound processing and analysis.
